        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: avoid DeepSeek-native thinking on OpenRouter V4",
        "body": "Fixes #97196\r\n\r\n## What Problem This Solves\r\n\r\nFixes an issue where users running OpenRouter-routed DeepSeek V4 models could hit a 400 response because OpenClaw sent both OpenRouter reasoning controls and DeepSeek-native thinking controls in the same request.\r\n\r\n## Why This Change Was Made\r\n\r\nOpenRouter DeepSeek V4 requests now stay on the OpenRouter reasoning payload shape (`reasoning.effort`) instead of adding DeepSeek-native `thinking` / `reasoning_effort` fields after the provider wrapper runs. The DeepSeek V4 replay repair still backfills `reasoning_content` only when OpenRouter reasoning remains enabled, and the core fallback now respects detected non-native thinking formats so unowned DeepSeek-compatible proxy routes keep their native fallback without breaking OpenRouter.\r\n\r\n## User Impact\r\n\r\nUsers can use `openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` and `openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` without the request being rejected for conflicting reasoning fields. `/think max` and stale max overrides still map to OpenRouter's supported `xhigh` effort.\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/openrouter/index.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/extra-params.deepseek-v4-thinking-format.test.ts`\r\n  - `extensions/openrouter/index.test.ts`: 43 passed\r\n  - `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/extra-params.deepseek-v4-thinking-format.test.ts`: 9 passed\r\n- `git diff --check`\r\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\r\n  - clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\r\n\r\nReal behavior proof still to add before ready-for-review:\r\n\r\n- Screenshot of a live OpenRouter DeepSeek V4 request succeeding from OpenClaw.\r\n- Screenshot or redacted log line showing the outbound request/request debug no longer contains top-level `reasoning_effort` or `thinking`, while `reasoning.effort` is present.\r\nLive OpenRouter DeepSeek V4 proof: the request reached openrouter for deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash, returned status=200, and produced the expected reply without the previous conflicting reasoning-fields error.\r\n<img width=\"796\" height=\"480\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/be54d75d-a455-4b55-93e8-805d83fdf4e2\" />\r\n\r\n",
